{
  "stem": "3848.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when I got on this locomotive, there was a whole bunch of railroad people all traveling towards the former border of Russia and Poland, which was about the area of Zhytomyr, a small town of Zhytomyr.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And from there, we were traveling toward Kiev.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All this, I didn't know what's going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, wherever the railroad was going, wherever they were pulling the people, that's where I was going-- with them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Slowly, we traveled through all of Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Russian government, I suppose, decided to gather all the railroad people that were behind because they call it [NON-ENGLISH] in the Ukraine, a Ukraine part of that one that was already being taken over by German-- by Germany.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they kept us behind.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were in Kiev.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We passed Poltava, Kharkov, and from there we went back and forth because they are also gathered other railroad people, and they joined our transport.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Where the Russian government decided to keep this whole transport of railroad people-- all of the areas that were taken by Germany, to hold them because they expected to go back.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- and take back over the land that Germany took, and have the railroad people right away ready to fix the broken rails, the bombarded stations so they could bring the soldiers there.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as-- for the-- for about six months, five to six months, we've been on a train just traveling back and forth and back and forth.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And while the Germans were coming, the Russians were retreating.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we landed in Moscow where they got out of all of the railroad people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was a plan by Stalin to make a railroad that goes around Moscow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was stationed in a monastery called-- in-- in the city of Zagorsk.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
